      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"Process J09B\\n\\n1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp.\\n2. Update the table J09B_temp with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG.\\n3. Apply the following rules to the J09B_temp table:\\n   3.1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR; ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n   3.2. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 = 0.\\n   3.3. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 between 500 and 599 (inclusive).\\n   3.4. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 between 900 and 999 (inclusive).\\n4. Join J09B_temp with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. Join the resulting table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for each record:\\n   - If sales data is present, take sales data and empty (null out) the net data fields.\\n   - Otherwise keep the net data and empty (null out) the sales data fields.\\n7. Export the final data from the table as a CSV file named J09B including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n8. Send the CSV file to the EVU team at meter.readings@evu.com.\\n9. Delete the temporary table J09B_temp after exporting the data.\"}",
            "id": "lc_3bdb4b84-35a6-4a52-bace-68d2dfe8b936"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "9a42dfce-6f58-4732-bef9-a4ee256ab216",
        "tool_call_id": "call_WQ6btWCMFT05BICdcjPiCYvv",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "Process J09B\n\n1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp.\n2. Update the table J09B_temp with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG.\n3. Apply the following rules to the J09B_temp table:\n   3.1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR; ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\".\n   3.2. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 = 0.\n   3.3. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 between 500 and 599 (inclusive).\n   3.4. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\" for all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 between 900 and 999 (inclusive).\n4. Join J09B_temp with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. Join the resulting table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare sales data and net data for each record:\n   - If sales data is present, take sales data and empty (null out) the net data fields.\n   - Otherwise keep the net data and empty (null out) the sales data fields.\n7. Export the final data from the table as a CSV file named J09B including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n8. Send the CSV file to the EVU team at meter.readings@evu.com.\n9. Delete the temporary table J09B_temp after exporting the data."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
